⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Windmill
node AFM · AFM · ⟦The Windmill:AFM:7386ab⟧

WHO   — The Windmill — the grand project
WHAT  — The regime's perpetual project (the Five-Year Plans): it justifies endless sacrifice and never delivers the promised comfort.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because tyrannies run on a glorious tomorrow that pays for today's suffering — the windmill is the carrot and the lash.
HOW   — By the animals' broken backs, rebuilt after every collapse, its credit claimed by Napoleon and its failures blamed on Snowball.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I was the promise of an easier life that justified every hard one — built on Boxer's back, my credit Napoleon's, my collapse always Snowball's fault.

